response.original_title: Dick Powell and Joan Blondell home movies: "No. 5"
response.overview: Silent home movies, in both black and white and color, of Dick Powell and Joan Blondell from around the time of their wedding. Footage features Joan modeling several different outfits and the two of them at the wedding of another couple. Includes clips from the Hearst Metrotone News segment Snapshots from here and there, with Powell and Blondell cutting the wedding cake, and the two of them on a boat with New York City in the background. Actress Helen Kane, musician/composer Roger Wolfe Kahn, and his wife, Edith May Nelson appear briefly in the footage.  From the collection of the UCLA Film & Television Archive.
response.title: Dick Powell and Joan Blondell home movies: "No. 5"
